```julia
function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return lowercase(strip(col)) * "_" * replace(lowercase(strip(col)), "-" => "_")
end
```

This function first strips any leading or trailing whitespaces from the `col` using `strip()` and then lowers the case of the remaining string. It then replaces all spaces and hyphens with underscores using `replace()`. The result is a lowercase column name with no spaces or hyphens, but with underscores instead.
